WEBVTT

02:07.261 --> 02:10.162
Sit. Sit.
Come back.

02:20.574 --> 02:22.040
A<i> pain au chocolat, </i>
bud?

02:22.042 --> 02:23.375
Please, one.

02:26.113 --> 02:27.713
Bud,

02:27.715 --> 02:30.315
I can't give you no more
for free, huh?

02:30.317 --> 02:32.818
Not every time.

02:32.820 --> 02:34.386
Not no more.

02:34.388 --> 02:35.554
I have to subsist.

02:35.556 --> 02:36.889
I know.
I know. I know.

02:36.891 --> 02:38.390
I--I don't carry money
when I run.

02:38.392 --> 02:41.360
I'll give it to you
tomorrow.

02:41.362 --> 02:44.496
- Tomorrow 100%?
- 100%.

02:44.498 --> 02:46.131
Lou come by,

02:46.133 --> 02:49.835
ask if you're feeding here
too much.

02:49.837 --> 02:51.170
Oh, that's 'cause
he thinks

02:51.172 --> 02:52.671
that I'm coming out
of retirement,

02:52.673 --> 02:54.940
but I'm not,
so this is okay.

02:54.942 --> 02:59.144
If you go back fighting,
you're heavyweight now.

02:59.146 --> 03:00.312
Not middleweight.

03:01.482 --> 03:03.448
- Come on. Let's go.
- Wait.

03:03.450 --> 03:04.449
Bye, Claude.

03:04.451 --> 03:07.252
Come on.
Come on.

03:43.123 --> 03:46.692
Hey.

03:46.694 --> 03:48.493
Hey, Hernandez,
no plantain for Silly.

03:49.496 --> 03:50.495
I'm serious, dude.

03:50.497 --> 03:51.730
She shits on the rug,

03:51.732 --> 03:52.731
and she feels
ashamed of herself.

03:52.733 --> 03:54.533
No plantains.

03:57.137 --> 03:59.705
Why does Hernandez always have
to mop the floor so diligently?

03:59.707 --> 04:00.872
It depresses the hell out of me.

04:00.874 --> 04:01.974
How do you mean?

04:01.976 --> 04:03.508
He's always mopping the floor

04:03.510 --> 04:04.509
like<i> LIFE</i> magazine
is gonna come,

04:04.511 --> 04:05.644
and they're not.

04:05.646 --> 04:07.079
He mops to mop.

04:07.081 --> 04:08.647
You're trying to change
the subject.

04:08.649 --> 04:10.015
From what?

04:10.017 --> 04:12.517
You working with me
training Kid Sunshine,

04:12.519 --> 04:13.652
like we talked about.

04:13.654 --> 04:15.354
I'm going to J.J.'s tonight.

04:15.356 --> 04:18.457
He wants to open a Bud's Place
in the city.

04:18.459 --> 04:20.025
J.J. huh?

04:20.027 --> 04:21.393
Just checking it out.

04:21.395 --> 04:22.761
Just being friendly.

04:24.364 --> 04:26.565
Okay, I'm intrigued.
What's his weight?

04:26.567 --> 04:28.600
159.

04:28.602 --> 04:30.102
We got to get him down
to welterweight.

04:30.104 --> 04:32.104
I thought you wanted to turn him
into Floyd Patterson.

04:32.106 --> 04:35.140
Mercury Williams' people
came to us last night--

04:35.142 --> 04:38.410
$500,000 and 2%
of the pay-per-view.

04:38.412 --> 04:40.112
For WBO at the Garden?

04:40.114 --> 04:42.581
I mean, really getting
shortchanged.

04:42.583 --> 04:45.684
But the point is, it's Madison
Square Garden next month.

04:45.686 --> 04:47.653
Kid goes for
the welterweight title.

04:47.655 --> 04:49.621
HBO wanted to bring
their cameras in here

04:49.623 --> 04:51.790
and shoot Kid training.

04:51.792 --> 04:54.293
"Behind the scenes,"
they called it.

04:54.295 --> 04:57.596
I told them no.

04:57.598 --> 04:58.930
You told them no?

04:58.932 --> 05:00.832
Relax.

05:00.834 --> 05:02.601
The fight is what's
consequential.

05:02.603 --> 05:04.636
Oh, the fight's what's
consequential.

05:04.638 --> 05:07.806
HBO's not consequential.
It's not consequential at all.

05:07.808 --> 05:09.207
It's just
the only game in town.

05:09.209 --> 05:11.610
<i> Boardwalk Empire's </i>
not consequential.

05:12.845 --> 05:16.148
<i> Girls</i> isn't consequential.

05:23.656 --> 05:27.826
Oh, Silly.

05:27.828 --> 05:30.128
You know how much coffee
costs these days?

05:30.130 --> 05:31.930
Uh, a buck fifty?

05:31.932 --> 05:33.598
You say that like it makes
some sort of sense.

05:33.600 --> 05:35.200
It does.

05:35.202 --> 05:37.235
It's a large cup, hot,
doesn't taste like ass.

05:37.237 --> 05:39.604
It's a decent deal.

05:39.606 --> 05:41.606
Can I have a section
of the paper?

05:41.608 --> 05:46.345
You can have the whole thing.
I'm gonna take a shower.

05:46.347 --> 05:47.979
How come you never get
<i> The Ledger?</i>

05:47.981 --> 05:49.514
Who cares what's happening
in Jersey?

05:49.516 --> 05:51.316
I do.
I fuckin' live here.

05:51.318 --> 05:52.351
You do too, you know.

05:52.353 --> 05:53.785
Don't remind me.

05:53.787 --> 05:56.254
No Broadway,
no Derek Jeter,

05:56.256 --> 05:59.057
no Rockefeller Center,
but I got you--

05:59.059 --> 06:01.026
my own personal
national treasure.

06:01.028 --> 06:04.229
You stink.
Take a shower!

06:06.899 --> 06:08.033
Sorry.

06:08.035 --> 06:09.935
I'm not used to you
wanting it all the time.

06:09.937 --> 06:11.269
I always want it
all the time.

06:11.271 --> 06:14.072
I was training.
I couldn't have it.

06:16.477 --> 06:17.409
What the fuck?

06:17.411 --> 06:18.677
The water's not hot.

06:18.679 --> 06:20.312
- Is it cold?
- It's lukewarm.

06:20.314 --> 06:22.180
Better take that.

06:23.983 --> 06:25.584
That doesn't bother you?
Lukewarm?

06:25.586 --> 06:29.187
You really should take a shower
while it's hot at all.

06:29.189 --> 06:30.922
What are you doing
with that pen?

06:30.924 --> 06:32.557
Better if you get
<i> The Ledger.</i>

06:32.559 --> 06:34.059
You're making me
depressed here.

06:34.061 --> 06:35.494
Give me a week,
a week and a half.

06:35.496 --> 06:37.429
All right?

06:37.431 --> 06:39.331
If I haven't gotten something
together by then,

06:39.333 --> 06:41.466
you can--you can do
whatever the fuck you want.

06:42.536 --> 06:43.769
Waitress at Beau Morley's.

06:43.771 --> 06:45.036
You trying to
make me depressed?

06:45.038 --> 06:46.505
I was circling
practical things.

06:46.507 --> 06:49.641
Well, you're making me
practically suicidal.

06:49.643 --> 06:51.610
Give me a week.
Okay?

06:51.612 --> 06:53.011
I know
I've been saying it,

06:53.013 --> 06:55.714
but things
are coming together.

06:55.716 --> 06:59.184
All right?
No red pen for a week.

06:59.186 --> 07:03.188
You're not gonna
make fun of me?

07:03.190 --> 07:04.923
Good.

07:07.360 --> 07:08.894
Let's go see a movie.

07:08.896 --> 07:12.931
Want to see a movie?

07:12.933 --> 07:15.300
You want to see a movie with me?

07:15.302 --> 07:16.301
De Niro?

07:16.303 --> 07:17.102
Yeah.

07:17.104 --> 07:18.403
That is truly terrible.

07:18.405 --> 07:19.738
Well, how'd you know
who it was, then?

07:19.740 --> 07:21.339
Oh, please.
Give it up.

07:21.341 --> 07:23.175
You won't see the
Sandra Bullock movie, right?

07:23.177 --> 07:24.443
Right.

07:24.445 --> 07:26.945
Well, I don't want to see
any action movies.

07:26.947 --> 07:28.947
- Oh--here we go.
- What?

07:28.949 --> 07:30.382
I'm allowed to not want to see
a bunch of people

07:30.384 --> 07:31.983
get killed today,
aren't I?

07:31.985 --> 07:33.485
I don't want to fucking fight
about it.

07:33.487 --> 07:35.320
I don't want to fucking
fight about it either.

07:35.322 --> 07:37.189
Look, just pick something.
I don't care what it is.

07:37.191 --> 07:40.392
I just want to sit
in a dark theater and kill time.

07:44.664 --> 07:46.364
I was thinking
I want to try auditing

07:46.366 --> 07:47.933
some classes at Columbia--

07:47.935 --> 07:50.769
Robert Thurman's classes
on Buddhism.

07:50.771 --> 07:52.237
Robert Thurman?

07:52.239 --> 07:54.639
You say that like
I'm supposed to know him.

07:54.641 --> 07:55.807
I know Thurman Munson.

07:55.809 --> 07:58.109
Robert Thurman was
the first white guy

07:58.111 --> 08:00.278
the Dalai Lama
ordained as a monk.

08:00.280 --> 08:03.181
And he's Uma Thurman's
father.

08:03.183 --> 08:05.183
He's a monk
and he's Uma Thurman's father?

08:05.185 --> 08:06.985
He resigned his monk's vows
of celibacy

08:06.987 --> 08:08.186
and married
a Swedish woman.

08:08.188 --> 08:10.355
Of course he did.

08:10.357 --> 08:14.359
She probably looked just like
Uma Thurman.

08:14.361 --> 08:19.097
What's--what's infinite nirvana
compared to Swedish skin?

08:19.099 --> 08:20.765
That's who you want to be
your teacher?

08:20.767 --> 08:23.368
I love it.
You never cease to amaze me.

08:23.370 --> 08:24.836
He gets a pass

08:24.838 --> 08:27.138
because he crammed with,
you know, holy-moly man,

08:27.140 --> 08:28.673
but the rest of us
can't get a break--

08:28.675 --> 08:30.509
Forget I fucking
mentioned it, okay?

08:30.511 --> 08:33.211
You don't get it.
It's not about being holy.

08:33.213 --> 08:35.547
It's about nothing
being sacred or holy.

08:35.549 --> 08:37.215
Tried to explain it, and
you don't fucking listen.

08:37.217 --> 08:38.817
Right, right.
I don't listen.

08:38.819 --> 08:41.520
It's me.
It's me.

08:45.057 --> 08:46.691
It's better with butter.

08:46.693 --> 08:48.793
There's still time
for you to get some butter.

08:48.795 --> 08:51.596
Please shut the fuck up.

08:51.598 --> 08:53.064
Oh, that's right.

08:53.066 --> 08:54.533
There's no--
there's no trailers here.

08:54.535 --> 08:55.834
Shh.

08:55.836 --> 08:57.035
I told you that
was gonna happen.

08:57.037 --> 08:58.503
You got one of them
Steve Jobs,

08:58.505 --> 09:00.372
and now all you do is check it
and check it and check it.

09:00.374 --> 09:01.773
I'm checking it constantly

09:01.775 --> 09:03.108
because I'm in
a state of disbelief.

09:03.110 --> 09:05.243
Nobody ever fucking texts
or calls anymore.

09:05.245 --> 09:07.045
It's like they gave me
the number of a ghost.

09:07.047 --> 09:09.114
Where have all
the hangers-on gone?

09:09.116 --> 09:11.016
You used to complain
about them being around.

09:11.018 --> 09:14.119
I've lost 73 Facebook friends
in the last few months.

09:14.121 --> 09:16.187
Your shoelaces
are untied.

09:17.890 --> 09:20.325
Are they really
your friends?

09:20.327 --> 09:22.594
Anyways, very least,
you can not check your phone

09:22.596 --> 09:24.329
in the middle
of the movie.

09:24.331 --> 09:26.898
Movies like that
bug the hell out of me.

09:26.900 --> 09:28.767
I mean, why don't they
just move?

09:28.769 --> 09:30.302
I thought the movie
was solid.

09:30.304 --> 09:32.137
So if you don't mind, I want
to be alone with my thoughts

09:32.139 --> 09:34.139
for a little bit before you
pollute me with your negativity.

09:34.141 --> 09:35.941
And where would they move?
Where are they gonna move?

09:35.943 --> 09:37.542
Far away.
You're in love.

09:37.544 --> 09:39.277
Some assholes tell you
not to fall in love.

09:39.279 --> 09:40.879
Move away from
the assholes.

09:40.881 --> 09:42.180
I think wherever
they went--

09:42.182 --> 09:43.481
They went--
please.

09:43.483 --> 09:45.216
They move to Rome.
They move to Paris.

09:45.218 --> 09:47.319
Who the fuck is gonna care?
They can do their own thing.

09:47.321 --> 09:48.820
They can lick pears
and chew salami.

09:48.822 --> 09:50.655
Even if you move,
your problems don't vanish.

09:50.657 --> 09:52.657
They do if your problem
is where you live.

09:52.659 --> 09:54.759
Oh, look!

09:59.733 --> 10:00.999
- Did you hear that?
- Yeah.

10:01.001 --> 10:02.233
It was
spitting something up.

10:02.235 --> 10:04.035
He was not.
He was laughing.

10:04.037 --> 10:05.604
I made him laugh.
You couldn't tell?

10:05.606 --> 10:08.006
Oh!
Ho-ho-ho!

10:08.008 --> 10:10.976
Uppercut, uppercut,
left, right, left.

10:10.978 --> 10:11.977
Right?

10:11.979 --> 10:13.645
Right.

10:13.647 --> 10:15.180
You want money, huh?

10:15.182 --> 10:16.648
They called you
The Saint.

10:16.650 --> 10:19.718
Yep.
You want money?

10:19.720 --> 10:20.719
I'm Ray.

10:20.721 --> 10:21.786
That's good.

10:21.788 --> 10:23.521
Don't be a fuck,
honey.

10:23.523 --> 10:26.224
That's okay, ma'am.
He ain't got to talk to me.

10:26.226 --> 10:28.994
Too bad your saint...

10:28.996 --> 10:30.528
didn't have a stronger chin.

10:31.565 --> 10:33.365
Oh, sure,
you had blazing speed

10:33.367 --> 10:35.800
but no whiskers.

10:35.802 --> 10:38.003
Jesus got hit hard,
but he stayed the course.

10:38.005 --> 10:39.170
Come on, Bud.

10:39.172 --> 10:40.271
You're a fuckin' bum.

10:40.273 --> 10:41.473
What do you know
about saints?

10:41.475 --> 10:43.108
I could smell you
all the way from here.

10:43.110 --> 10:44.309
Oh, so what?
I smell.

10:44.311 --> 10:46.011
You never heard of
Saint Francis,

10:46.013 --> 10:47.078
ignorant motherfucker?

10:47.080 --> 10:48.980
Here, here,
take this.

10:48.982 --> 10:50.882
Oh, no, that's okay, ma'am.
That's fine. I'm fine.

10:50.884 --> 10:53.718
Thank you very much, ma'am,
kindly.

10:53.720 --> 10:56.788
You should absorb some dignity
from your woman, Saint.

10:56.790 --> 10:57.922
Wouldn't kill you.

10:57.924 --> 10:59.357
We're done.
Come on.

10:59.359 --> 11:02.394
Wise men may be free of greed
but not you.

11:02.396 --> 11:03.995
I can't believe you tried

11:03.997 --> 11:05.797
to give that
rambling twat $2.

11:05.799 --> 11:07.365
It's cold.

11:07.367 --> 11:09.134
Yeah, I know.
I'm fucking freezing.

11:09.136 --> 11:10.568
Did I tell you
how those yogis

11:10.570 --> 11:12.103
generate heat in the cold
through meditation?

11:12.105 --> 11:13.571
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

11:13.573 --> 11:15.407
You told me something about
the breathing techniques

11:15.409 --> 11:17.008
to fire up the heart pulmonary
or something.

11:17.010 --> 11:18.543
That's not exactly it.

11:18.545 --> 11:20.879
Well, it had something to do
with breathing.

11:20.881 --> 11:22.714
Sorry.
I'm not a yogi.

11:24.784 --> 11:26.051
How late you gonna be?

11:26.053 --> 11:27.585
If it goes good, late.

11:27.587 --> 11:30.622
He might want to drink
or watch fights or something.

11:30.624 --> 11:34.392
Text me if you're gonna be out
all night.

11:34.394 --> 11:35.193
Good luck.

13:17.096 --> 13:19.798
Welcome to
The Silver Apple.

13:23.302 --> 13:26.004
I parked out front,
in front of the fire hydrant--

13:26.006 --> 13:27.572
Yeah, that's my spot.
Cops know that.

13:27.574 --> 13:29.107
I got, like,
a shitty car.

13:29.109 --> 13:31.176
Hey,
that's my spot.

13:31.178 --> 13:32.377
Whoever parks there
is with me.

13:32.379 --> 13:36.247
Don't be so dubious.

13:36.249 --> 13:39.083
They closed
your restaurant.

13:39.085 --> 13:41.252
You know, people in Jersey
don't have any taste.

13:41.254 --> 13:43.922
I should have known
not to bother with them.

13:43.924 --> 13:46.624
All that money
down the drain.

13:46.626 --> 13:49.260
What are you doing
for work now?

13:49.262 --> 13:50.562
Lou wants me
to work with him.

13:50.564 --> 13:52.564
Work with this kid,
uh, Kid Sunshine.

13:52.566 --> 13:54.432
Teach him the science
of the game.

13:54.434 --> 13:56.167
Hit and don't get hit,
no?

13:56.169 --> 13:57.502
You say that
like it's easy.

13:57.504 --> 13:59.170
It's easier said
than done.

13:59.172 --> 14:00.905
No, I believe you.
I believe you.

14:00.907 --> 14:03.141
But Lou Powell...

14:05.644 --> 14:07.579
Thank you, sweetheart.

14:07.581 --> 14:11.382
He digs the smell
of sweat and piss.

14:11.384 --> 14:13.785
Lou don't care if
it's MSG or VFW halls.

14:13.787 --> 14:15.854
He's a gym rat.
Well, hooray for him.

14:15.856 --> 14:16.888
Whatever's clever,

14:16.890 --> 14:18.323
but you're someone

14:18.325 --> 14:20.692
who's not afraid
of the finer things.

14:20.694 --> 14:22.026
Am I right?

14:23.029 --> 14:24.562
Mm-hmm.

14:24.564 --> 14:26.197
Yes, that's pure silver
you're holding, by the way.

14:26.199 --> 14:28.299
You feel the weight?

14:30.769 --> 14:32.871
Why don't you come work for me
for a little while?

14:32.873 --> 14:33.872
Hmm?

14:33.874 --> 14:36.241
Pickups. Deliveries.

14:36.243 --> 14:38.676
You go around the city
with Roberto.

14:38.678 --> 14:42.013
Make sure everybody
we associate with is--

14:42.015 --> 14:43.448
is full of good cheer.

14:43.450 --> 14:45.216
I must warn you of one thing,
though.

14:45.218 --> 14:46.517
What's that?

14:46.519 --> 14:48.653
He listens to glam rock
all day on the radio,

14:48.655 --> 14:50.521
so if you're similar to me,
you're gonna have to

14:50.523 --> 14:52.523
figure something out--
some kind of arrangement.

14:52.525 --> 14:56.527
I used to like the
New York Dolls, not no more.

14:56.529 --> 14:59.564
What kind of music you got
on your iPod?

15:02.001 --> 15:04.435
Oh, fuck me.
Is that a Walkman?

15:04.437 --> 15:05.803
Well, I-I got an iPhone.

15:05.805 --> 15:08.806
I just don't have
any music for it.

15:08.808 --> 15:11.376
I believe it's important
to turn yourself completely over

15:11.378 --> 15:14.045
to digital technology.

15:14.047 --> 15:17.015
My entire life...

15:17.017 --> 15:18.349
is in the iCloud.

15:18.351 --> 15:20.885
What kind of music
you dig on?

15:20.887 --> 15:24.255
Uh, Laura Nyro.
It's this beatnik chick.

15:24.257 --> 15:26.925
My--my girl recommended her.

15:26.927 --> 15:29.827
I-I don't really listen
to anything other than

15:29.829 --> 15:31.529
what she has in
her cassette collection.

15:31.531 --> 15:33.965
She never got into iTunes
or anything.

15:33.967 --> 15:35.700
She never even got into CDs.

15:35.702 --> 15:38.303
You know, I never used to
listen to anything.

15:38.305 --> 15:42.006
You know, Lou says
that you should never jog

15:42.008 --> 15:43.374
with music.

15:43.376 --> 15:45.410
Says if you run to
the theme song to<i> Rocky,</i>

15:45.412 --> 15:46.878
you'll just be
a bitch fighter.

15:46.880 --> 15:48.413
Well, he doesn't say
the word "bitch," though.

15:48.415 --> 15:49.881
He says
"sentimental fighter."

15:49.883 --> 15:50.815
Sentimental fighter?

15:50.817 --> 15:52.183
Yeah,
an emotional fighter.

15:52.185 --> 15:53.451
Lou says the worst thing
you can be

15:53.453 --> 15:56.421
is an emotional fighter.

15:56.423 --> 15:58.823
You know,
that's why it's science.

15:58.825 --> 16:00.725
You know, you got to be
like a scientist.

16:00.727 --> 16:03.328
Otherwise, you get all
emotionally involved

16:03.330 --> 16:04.963
and unbalanced.

16:04.965 --> 16:07.298
Yeah.

16:07.300 --> 16:09.801
You see my face
right now?

16:09.803 --> 16:12.971
This is me marveling.

16:12.973 --> 16:15.907
I marvel at you lads.

16:15.909 --> 16:18.042
You're monks in the gym.

16:18.044 --> 16:19.811
The most peaceful place
on earth.

16:19.813 --> 16:21.879
Oh, the sound of the--

16:21.881 --> 16:26.050
the ropes and the bags
and the breathing.

16:26.052 --> 16:29.620
It's funny that it all
leads towards violence.

16:29.622 --> 16:33.825
Hmm?
All that peacefulness.

16:34.961 --> 16:36.060
But, hey,
what do I know?

16:37.497 --> 16:40.431
I know one thing;

16:40.433 --> 16:43.234
I want The Saint

16:43.236 --> 16:45.770
and his scientific mind

16:45.772 --> 16:48.906
on my side.

16:48.908 --> 16:51.309
Roberto fights dogs,
doesn't he?

16:51.311 --> 16:53.077
I got nothing to do
with the dog fighting

16:53.079 --> 16:54.445
and neither will you.

16:54.447 --> 16:56.547
You just go around with him
for a couple of weeks,

16:56.549 --> 16:57.815
and in the meantime,

16:57.817 --> 16:59.984
we start bringing
your restaurant down here

16:59.986 --> 17:02.687
to the West Village.

17:05.457 --> 17:07.925
You mean like it was in Jersey
but in Manhattan?

17:07.927 --> 17:09.427
Exactly.

17:09.429 --> 17:12.363
Oh, I dug your place.

17:12.365 --> 17:14.599
Bud's.
Hmm?

17:14.601 --> 17:18.803
I mean, this place here,
it's all trumps and strumpets,

17:18.805 --> 17:20.705
but Bud's...

17:20.707 --> 17:23.875
An everyday guy can watch
a fight, lay down a bet,

17:23.877 --> 17:25.743
and I'll own it, of course,
but after a while,

17:25.745 --> 17:30.915
you make enough money;
you buy a stake...

17:30.917 --> 17:34.352
We become partners.

17:34.354 --> 17:38.523
I even got a spot
picked out.

17:38.525 --> 17:43.494
So it'll be Bud's,

17:43.496 --> 17:48.466
or it'll be
some other guy's.

17:48.468 --> 17:51.102
What say you?

17:54.740 --> 17:57.375
Let's break out the special
California chardonnay.

17:57.377 --> 17:58.910
Pour yourself a glass too.

17:58.912 --> 18:03.147
Oh, I get to drink
with the big shots?

18:03.149 --> 18:05.616
Wow.

18:05.618 --> 18:09.387
She's not normally
so trenchant.

18:09.389 --> 18:11.923
She must have
a schoolgirl crush on you.

18:11.925 --> 18:13.624
Oh, yeah.

18:13.626 --> 18:16.027
You seen her over
from back in the day?

18:16.029 --> 18:17.762
<i> S.I.</i> swimsuit pics?

18:17.764 --> 18:19.764
Oh, you fuckin' monk.

18:19.766 --> 18:24.302
She was 19
with no top off.

18:24.304 --> 18:25.870
Ow.

18:30.742 --> 18:32.176
She was versatile too.

18:32.178 --> 18:34.078
She could do the beach.
She could do heroin chic.

18:34.080 --> 18:36.214
That was a great time
in fashion.

18:36.216 --> 18:39.817
I miss heroin chic badly.

18:39.819 --> 18:42.320
It'll come back, though.

18:42.322 --> 18:47.258
Emaciated, suicidal teen
haute couture.

18:47.260 --> 18:48.960
Ooh.

18:48.962 --> 18:52.163
Still there
if you look closely.

18:55.901 --> 18:59.403
Yup.

18:59.405 --> 19:00.404
Ah, I forgot.
I gotta--

19:00.406 --> 19:02.740
Hey, Champ!

19:02.742 --> 19:04.008
Hey.
How's it going?

19:04.010 --> 19:05.376
Hey. Why are you so tight?

19:05.378 --> 19:06.844
What's going on?

19:06.846 --> 19:08.079
You're smelling good.
What--

19:08.081 --> 19:09.647
What is that?
What fragrance is that?

19:09.649 --> 19:10.648
What are you wearing?

19:10.650 --> 19:11.816
It's CK Obsession.

19:11.818 --> 19:13.684
You got to let me
borrow that.

19:13.686 --> 19:15.386
They sell it
everywhere.

19:15.388 --> 19:18.656
I want to share with you.

19:18.658 --> 19:20.858
J.J., you got a sec?

19:20.860 --> 19:25.129
I got to jaw with you,
man.

19:25.131 --> 19:26.998
Been watching
MSG fights?

19:27.000 --> 19:29.167
No, I've been with
my friend here.

19:29.169 --> 19:31.035
Can't you see that?

19:31.037 --> 19:33.104
Yeah, I see that.

19:33.106 --> 19:34.705
It can wait.

19:34.707 --> 19:36.807
I can tell you now,
or I can tell you later

19:36.809 --> 19:38.376
and you'll be mad at me.

19:38.378 --> 19:42.647
You'll make me join the
Church of Scientology with you.

19:42.649 --> 19:45.583
Washington went down
in the 12th.

19:45.585 --> 19:48.686
A real barn burner!

19:48.688 --> 19:50.354
Drink.
Come on.

19:50.356 --> 19:52.557
We'll be back.

19:52.559 --> 19:54.859
I know a lot of good shit
about you, man.

19:57.496 --> 19:59.430
They won't be back.

19:59.432 --> 20:00.431
No?

20:00.433 --> 20:02.433
No.

20:02.435 --> 20:04.001
Text Ellen.

20:04.003 --> 20:05.436
I should call her.

20:05.438 --> 20:07.138
Text her.

20:07.140 --> 20:09.073
Tell her you're staying at
a hotel for the night.

20:09.075 --> 20:11.509
You--you're too drunk
to drive.

20:11.511 --> 20:13.077
You are, by the way.

20:13.079 --> 20:15.746
Is there, like, a--is there
a Holiday Inn or something?

20:15.748 --> 20:17.748
Don't know.
Don't do dumps.

20:17.750 --> 20:19.317
Oh, you say that like
I have a choice.

20:19.319 --> 20:22.119
I don't even have
hot water.

20:22.121 --> 20:25.323
We can't have you staying
at the Holiday Inn

20:25.325 --> 20:28.025
all alone and all pale.

20:30.395 --> 20:32.396
I get off in an hour.

20:32.398 --> 20:34.365
I got a guest room
at my place.

20:34.367 --> 20:38.236
You'll have your own bathroom
with a shower,

20:38.238 --> 20:40.238
Bud.

21:18.043 --> 21:21.579
Come on.
Go to his body. Come on.

21:22.715 --> 21:24.682
Side to side.
Side to side.

21:24.684 --> 21:26.517
All right. Good. Good.
Keep coming in.

21:26.519 --> 21:27.551
Coming in.
Yeah.

21:27.553 --> 21:30.021
All right, Kid.

21:30.023 --> 21:31.689
That's it.

21:31.691 --> 21:34.325
All right. Good.
Keep coming in.

21:34.327 --> 21:37.895
- On your toes. That's it.
- All right.

21:37.897 --> 21:41.265
- Good.
- Step into him.

21:44.070 --> 21:45.536
- Good.
- That's it.

21:45.538 --> 21:46.837
That's right.
That's right.

21:46.839 --> 21:48.072
- Get him off him.
- That's it.

21:48.074 --> 21:49.507
Good. Good.

21:49.509 --> 21:51.709
- Stay on him.
- Stay. Stay.

21:54.313 --> 21:56.414
- All right. Back it up.
- Don't let him off the hook.

21:56.416 --> 21:57.982
That's right.
That's good.

21:57.984 --> 21:59.250
Do it again.
That's right.

21:59.252 --> 22:01.852
You're gonna help Lou
train Kid,

22:01.854 --> 22:04.255
but you're also committed
to J.J. Cook.

22:04.257 --> 22:05.423
Right.

22:05.425 --> 22:06.891
Sounds conflicting.

22:06.893 --> 22:08.392
Look, it's not like
I told Lou

22:08.394 --> 22:09.860
I was gonna be at
the gym forever.

22:09.862 --> 22:11.762
I just said I'd--I'd help him
with Kid Sunshine

22:11.764 --> 22:13.631
for this title fight;
by the time we have to

22:13.633 --> 22:15.566
move to Manhattan,
the fight'll be over.

22:15.568 --> 22:17.501
You've got it all
figured out.

22:17.503 --> 22:18.569
You know, I thought
you'd be happy.

22:18.571 --> 22:19.870
This way,
if this works,

22:19.872 --> 22:21.872
you don't have to work
that shitty job.

22:21.874 --> 22:24.675
You could be maître d'
at Bud's like before.

22:24.677 --> 22:27.144
How was the Holiday Inn?

22:27.146 --> 22:29.880
Asleep the second I got there.

22:29.882 --> 22:31.916
Why do I feel like
my good news is bad news here?

22:31.918 --> 22:33.384
It's a big move, is all.

22:33.386 --> 22:35.586
It's a couple U-Haul vans.
We've moved before.

22:35.588 --> 22:38.022
From two blocks away.

22:38.024 --> 22:40.725
Don't you miss having, like,
a big, nice place like before?

22:40.727 --> 22:42.360
That place was party-worthy.

22:42.362 --> 22:44.528
I honestly don't miss it.

22:44.530 --> 22:46.297
To me,
this place is cozy.

22:46.299 --> 22:48.065
Even if we had a baby,
I think we could stay here--

22:48.067 --> 22:51.268
Please, don't
get on that again.

22:51.270 --> 22:53.671
Sorry.

22:53.673 --> 22:55.506
All right,
what's your weight today?

22:55.508 --> 22:57.007
156.

22:57.009 --> 22:59.310
All right, you got to lose
9, 10 in the next few weeks.

22:59.312 --> 23:00.511
I can do it.

23:00.513 --> 23:01.712
Stay away from
the sweet stuff,

23:01.714 --> 23:03.147
and I'm not talking
about candy.

23:03.149 --> 23:04.415
Right.

23:04.417 --> 23:05.883
It's hot in here.
Makes you feel tired, huh?

23:05.885 --> 23:07.084
Nah, I'm fine.

23:07.086 --> 23:07.918
You drink?

23:07.920 --> 23:09.019
- Nah.
- Sleep around?

23:09.021 --> 23:11.021
- Nope.
- That's good.

23:11.023 --> 23:13.624
All right, to the body.

23:13.626 --> 23:16.694
Now to the head.

23:16.696 --> 23:18.996
To the body.

23:20.799 --> 23:22.633
Generate momentum
off the toe.

23:22.635 --> 23:24.535
Off the toe, not the heel.
Come on.

23:24.537 --> 23:27.304
Get it up.
Get it up.

23:28.940 --> 23:30.241
See?

23:30.243 --> 23:32.109
All right.
All right, all right, all right.

23:32.111 --> 23:34.011
Hit the lockers.

23:38.383 --> 23:39.850
Thanks, Saint.

23:39.852 --> 23:40.885
Don't mention it.

23:40.887 --> 23:44.555
Hey,
let me see your hands.

23:44.557 --> 23:45.689
Who taped your hands today?

23:45.691 --> 23:46.891
My homeboy Lonnie.

23:46.893 --> 23:48.292
No more Lonnie.

23:48.294 --> 23:49.527
I'll do it tomorrow.

23:49.529 --> 23:52.863
It's too tight.
There's too much tape.

24:03.009 --> 24:04.442
What are you looking at,
old man?

24:04.444 --> 24:05.810
Nothing.

24:05.812 --> 24:07.278
You're smiling about something.

24:07.280 --> 24:10.581
I suppose
I'm smiling because...

24:10.583 --> 24:12.750
you're having fun.

24:12.752 --> 24:14.418
Hell I am, man.

24:14.420 --> 24:15.886
It's disgusting here.

24:15.888 --> 24:17.688
It's full of sweat
and old memories.

24:17.690 --> 24:20.458
Sure. Sure.

24:21.960 --> 24:24.762
Good night, old man.

24:24.764 --> 24:28.065
Silly, come on.

24:35.407 --> 24:37.308
Silly?

24:37.310 --> 24:38.576
You seen Silly?

24:38.578 --> 24:42.480
I saw her about
five minutes ago.

24:42.482 --> 24:44.348
Silly?
Come on, girl.

24:46.785 --> 24:49.320
Hernandez,
you seen Silly?

24:51.490 --> 24:54.358
Silly?

24:54.360 --> 24:56.861
Come on, girl.

24:58.597 --> 25:00.231
Silly, is that you?

25:02.902 --> 25:04.435
What are you doing
in there?

25:10.510 --> 25:12.042
Hey, chill, man.

25:12.044 --> 25:13.244
Put down the guns--

25:13.246 --> 25:14.211
Is this your car?

25:14.213 --> 25:15.713
Well, look who's
driving Bimmers.

25:15.715 --> 25:17.081
Is this your fucking car?

25:17.083 --> 25:18.482
Damn skippy.
Can't you see the resemblance?

25:18.484 --> 25:19.450
That's my fucking dog!

25:19.452 --> 25:21.418
I know.
I took her for a joyride.

25:21.420 --> 25:22.419
You were training.

25:22.421 --> 25:24.154
Gave your pooch a couple
of frankfurters.

25:24.156 --> 25:25.556
Pooch loves frankfurters,
you know that?

25:25.558 --> 25:26.724
Yeah, I know that.

25:26.726 --> 25:27.725
She'll eat whatever
you give her.

25:27.727 --> 25:28.759
She'll even eat plantains.

25:28.761 --> 25:29.760
Give a pooch fruit?

25:29.762 --> 25:30.761
I don't understand that.

25:30.763 --> 25:32.029
Give a pooch meat,

25:32.031 --> 25:33.564
breed the killer instinct
in them--

25:33.566 --> 25:35.099
that I understand.

25:35.101 --> 25:37.134
Pooch will even eat
another pooch, you know that?

25:37.136 --> 25:38.669
Yeah, it depends
on the dog.

25:38.671 --> 25:40.337
No, no, no.
Any pooch.

25:40.339 --> 25:41.772
Fuck anything too.

25:41.774 --> 25:43.307
Well, the vet
took care of that.

25:43.309 --> 25:44.275
Ouch.

25:44.277 --> 25:47.811
Still, pooch
would fuck anything.

25:47.813 --> 25:49.046
Could you let her out,
please?

25:49.048 --> 25:51.615
Kind of muscular,
your dog,

25:51.617 --> 25:52.917
You ever think
of fighting her?

25:52.919 --> 25:54.585
- No.
- Why not?

25:54.587 --> 25:56.820
It's not just pits.
That's a common misconception.

25:56.822 --> 25:58.389
Yeah, I know.
I'm not into that. Okay?

25:58.391 --> 25:59.623
It's not humane.

25:59.625 --> 26:02.526
It's kind of funny
coming from a boxer, no?

26:02.528 --> 26:03.994
No.

26:03.996 --> 26:05.496
Whatever.

26:05.498 --> 26:07.331
If you ever change your mind,
let me know.

26:07.333 --> 26:11.035
Can make big bills,
the three of us.

26:11.037 --> 26:13.137
Can you let her out, please?
The windows are rolled up.

26:13.139 --> 26:14.905
It's cold; I didn't want her
to catch a cold.

26:14.907 --> 26:16.206
It's fucking frosty
out here.

26:16.208 --> 26:18.008
Please just unlock the door.
I got to go home.

26:18.010 --> 26:19.743
No.
We're working tonight.

26:19.745 --> 26:20.811
Tonight?

26:20.813 --> 26:22.046
Or should I call J.J.

26:22.048 --> 26:23.280
and tell him
you're not up for it?

26:23.282 --> 26:24.815
No, no, no.
I'm up for it.

26:24.817 --> 26:26.750
Great.
Let's rock and roll.

26:26.752 --> 26:28.786
All right, you know,
I got to--

26:28.788 --> 26:30.287
I got to go change.
I'm stinky.

26:30.289 --> 26:35.092
And put on that aromatic
Calvin Klein scent?

26:35.094 --> 26:36.460
Don't fret about it.

26:36.462 --> 26:38.562
We got to get to know
each other anyways.

26:38.564 --> 26:39.697
Oh.

26:39.699 --> 26:42.232
J.J. told me
to give you this.

26:42.234 --> 26:45.803
He loaded it with all that
crappy music you like.

26:45.805 --> 26:47.438
Let's go.

27:37.556 --> 27:39.757
We're gonna have to leave
the pooch in the car.

27:39.759 --> 27:42.026
The guy we're gonna go see
has a cat.

27:42.028 --> 27:43.560
I don't know.

27:43.562 --> 27:46.730
Dude, my boy runs
this fucking joint.

27:46.732 --> 27:49.233
Nobody's gonna fuck around
with my whip anyways.

27:49.235 --> 27:51.935
It's only gonna be
15 minutes.

27:51.937 --> 27:53.203
All right.

27:53.205 --> 27:55.639
We'll be right back.
Stay here.

27:59.811 --> 28:01.145
Yo, check this shit.

28:03.549 --> 28:05.349
Cuban heel, yo.

28:05.351 --> 28:06.784
You know what I'm saying?
Cuban heels.

28:06.786 --> 28:08.585
Yeah, I like--
I like that whole dance too.

28:08.587 --> 28:10.287
Yeah, fucking right
you like it.

28:10.289 --> 28:13.190
That's some fucking
Riverdance shit.

28:22.200 --> 28:25.536
I want to do, like, a crazy
Miles Davis voice for this.

28:25.538 --> 28:26.837
So just play along.

28:26.839 --> 28:27.871
Okay.

28:41.086 --> 28:43.020
Jeez.

28:48.126 --> 28:50.294
Gee whiz.

28:50.296 --> 28:52.096
Can we come in?

28:52.098 --> 28:54.431
This is my pal Bud.

28:54.433 --> 28:56.834
Boy, uh,

28:56.836 --> 28:58.469
I was just getting ready
for bed.

28:58.471 --> 29:01.138
Oh, we just walked up
all the stairs.

29:01.140 --> 29:03.006
Maybe we could all have
a glass of milk together

29:03.008 --> 29:04.708
before bed.

29:04.710 --> 29:06.376
I don't have any milk.

29:06.378 --> 29:09.580
You're being rude,
Stanley.

29:17.155 --> 29:18.956
Since it's your bedtime,

29:18.958 --> 29:21.391
straight,
no chaser.

29:23.161 --> 29:24.862
You owe 10 grand to J.J.

29:24.864 --> 29:26.530
That's more than I owe.
No?

29:26.532 --> 29:28.999
I explained our system to you
last time.

29:29.001 --> 29:31.735
You pay interest for every week
you don't pay.

29:34.172 --> 29:35.272
Don't I know you?

29:35.274 --> 29:36.974
He's Bud Gordon.

29:36.976 --> 29:38.709
Gee whiz.

29:38.711 --> 29:41.011
Why do I know
that name?

29:41.013 --> 29:43.280
The Saint.

29:43.282 --> 29:46.116
Bud "The Saint" Gordon?

29:46.118 --> 29:47.885
I lost money on you.

29:49.221 --> 29:52.156
You beat the hell out of Jackson
for four rounds.

29:52.158 --> 29:55.926
He punches you hard once
in the fifth,

29:55.928 --> 29:57.394
and you're out.

29:57.396 --> 30:01.732
Boy, that was some
disappointment for me.

30:01.734 --> 30:03.133
Yeah, for me too.

30:03.135 --> 30:05.636
With the Garden cheering you,

30:05.638 --> 30:07.371
I thought for sure

30:07.373 --> 30:12.042
this scrawny kid from Atlanta
is not gonna take the title.

30:12.044 --> 30:14.912
He was long,
like Tommy Hearns.

30:14.914 --> 30:18.015
Tommy Hearns
my ass.

30:18.017 --> 30:20.017
He lost his belt
the next fight

30:20.019 --> 30:22.019
to some kid
from the Poconos.

30:22.021 --> 30:26.990
Eh, the whole thing
made me shit funny.

30:26.992 --> 30:29.126
If we look under your mattress,

30:29.128 --> 30:33.897
in a Hefty bag,
there's how much?

30:33.899 --> 30:37.434
$300.

30:37.436 --> 30:40.904
No. $275.
I had Chinese delivered.

30:47.580 --> 30:49.513
Hutch!

30:49.515 --> 30:50.547
Put him down,
will you?

30:50.549 --> 30:52.216
I'm taking fucking Hutch.

30:52.218 --> 30:54.751
You can't.
He'll die without his insulin.

30:54.753 --> 30:56.086
He's diabetic.

30:56.088 --> 30:57.454
Just put him down,
will you?

30:57.456 --> 30:59.523
Wait, wait,
you're good for the money?

30:59.525 --> 31:00.724
Yes.

31:00.726 --> 31:02.259
Or you got somebody who can
lend you some money?

31:02.261 --> 31:03.427
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
yeah, yeah.

31:03.429 --> 31:04.895
Please don't take Hutch.

31:04.897 --> 31:07.631
He needs his shots.
You're holding him all wrong.

31:07.633 --> 31:09.433
He doesn't like to be held
like that.

31:09.435 --> 31:10.901
He's good for it.
Look at the man.

31:10.903 --> 31:12.636
I don't know.
It's a lot of money.

31:12.638 --> 31:16.139
Come on, man.
He's good for it.

31:16.141 --> 31:19.443
I'm gonna listen to
my associate tonight, Stanley.

31:19.445 --> 31:23.513
We'll both find out
if he makes good choices.

31:23.515 --> 31:25.616
Come here.
Come here, boy.

31:25.618 --> 31:27.050
Come here, Hutch.

31:27.052 --> 31:28.819
Oh, Hutch.

31:28.821 --> 31:30.287
Stanley,

31:30.289 --> 31:33.523
you got any Chinese food left?

31:33.525 --> 31:35.225
I look fucking amazing
eating noodles.

31:35.227 --> 31:36.760
Look at this.

31:39.898 --> 31:41.098
Hey, uh,

31:41.100 --> 31:43.100
hey, mind if I ask you
something?

31:43.102 --> 31:44.668
What?

31:44.670 --> 31:48.038
Were you really gonna
take his cat?

31:48.040 --> 31:49.306
Dude,

31:49.308 --> 31:51.475
I go into this shit--

31:51.477 --> 31:53.644
I'm Johnny Thunders
going into a guitar solo.

31:53.646 --> 31:57.381
I don't know how the fuck
it's gonna go down.

31:57.383 --> 32:00.117
So what's gonna happen
with Stanley now?

32:00.119 --> 32:02.886
Come here.

32:02.888 --> 32:04.254
Stand here.

32:06.724 --> 32:09.026
Hold on.
Wait.

32:09.028 --> 32:10.360
Have a--
have a baby carrot.

32:10.362 --> 32:11.895
It's okay.
I'm not hungry.

