Go get some water for Kid,
please.

47:19.070 --> 47:20.469
Small bottle.

47:20.471 --> 47:23.539
I don't want him
drinking much.

47:23.541 --> 47:24.874
Stretch it.

48:15.627 --> 48:19.161
Are you getting the paper
as well?

48:24.101 --> 48:25.368
Would you like
to make a donation

48:25.370 --> 48:28.537
to the Make-A-Wish
Foundation?

48:38.616 --> 48:40.349
Hey, you need me, Lou?

48:40.351 --> 48:42.318
I'm giving Kid a rubdown.

48:42.320 --> 48:45.254
I thought after, you could do
some footwork drills with him.

48:45.256 --> 48:47.390
How about tomorrow?

48:47.392 --> 48:49.191
- Everything all right?
- Yeah. Yeah.

48:49.193 --> 48:50.359
I'll see you tomorrow, Kid.

48:50.361 --> 48:52.695
All right, Saint.
You good?

48:52.697 --> 48:54.530
Yeah.

49:27.464 --> 49:30.433
- Hola.
- Roberto?

49:30.435 --> 49:33.302
You know what time it is, man?

49:33.304 --> 49:35.204
It's in the fucking paper,
man.

49:35.206 --> 49:36.706
- What?
- You killed him?

49:38.009 --> 49:39.275
You fucking shot him?

49:39.277 --> 49:40.476
Hey, hey.

49:40.478 --> 49:43.446
You should talk to J.J.
about that.

49:43.448 --> 49:45.614
Okay?
Big comandante J.J.

49:45.616 --> 49:46.949
Too high for me, partner.

49:46.951 --> 49:48.985
No, no, I'm not your
fucking partner anymore.

49:48.987 --> 49:50.252
That's over.

49:50.254 --> 49:52.488
I don't think so, man.

49:52.490 --> 49:55.424
Told you J.J. owned people.

49:55.426 --> 49:57.393
One of the people he owns
is Colby's super.

49:57.395 --> 50:00.930
J.J. has video footage
of you in the lobby,

50:00.932 --> 50:03.165
your beautiful face.

50:03.167 --> 50:06.702
<i> Claro,</i> that's not
what the cops have, though.

50:06.704 --> 50:10.072
Our super gave him
some looped-up shit.

50:10.074 --> 50:11.841
You ain't in that version.

50:11.843 --> 50:14.343
Course,
that's how it is now.

50:14.345 --> 50:17.747
Things change.
Your situation is pliable.

50:17.749 --> 50:20.916
It's up to you, bro,

50:20.918 --> 50:23.085
if you want to be
in the clear or not.

50:23.087 --> 50:26.122
Me, I'm gonna cozy on up

50:26.124 --> 50:27.957
and go to sleepy time.

50:31.629 --> 50:33.796
Bye.

50:37.367 --> 50:39.535
Um, it's over on McDonald.

50:39.537 --> 50:40.870
Yeah, it's really nice.

50:40.872 --> 50:43.239
But I only take her,
like, once a year.

50:43.241 --> 50:45.274
And every time,
they tell me,

50:45.276 --> 50:46.842
"She's so big."

50:48.713 --> 50:49.912
Do you want to get that?

50:49.914 --> 50:51.213
Or somebody else got it?

50:51.215 --> 50:52.848
Yeah, I think they got it
in the back.

50:52.850 --> 50:54.350
Yeah, don't worry about it.

50:54.352 --> 50:55.918
- I hope.
- I know. Right?

50:56.921 --> 51:00.022
- Is Ronnie working today?
- Yeah.

51:00.024 --> 51:01.757
Anyway, sorry,
you were saying.

51:01.759 --> 51:03.592
So you only take her
once a year, anyway, but--

51:03.594 --> 51:04.794
Yeah.

51:04.796 --> 51:06.162
Because I always get worried

51:06.164 --> 51:07.663
about, like,
how often you're supposed

51:07.665 --> 51:09.065
to take 'em in for shots
and everything.

51:09.067 --> 51:10.066
- Yeah.
- Anyway.

51:10.068 --> 51:11.434
- Hey.
- Hey.

51:11.436 --> 51:13.502
Were you wanting anything?

51:17.174 --> 51:20.109
Coffee.

51:20.111 --> 51:22.178
You're not eating?

51:22.180 --> 51:23.212
You see these spoons?

51:23.214 --> 51:24.680
The spoons are fine.

51:24.682 --> 51:26.215
Yeah, if you like someone
else's clam chowder.

51:26.217 --> 51:27.616
Picking a fight
with the Starlight?

51:27.618 --> 51:29.351
- Not hungry.
- Oh, yeah, sure. Since when?

51:29.353 --> 51:30.686
Okay, listen to me,
just listen.

51:30.688 --> 51:33.556
Something bad happened
last night.

51:33.558 --> 51:36.459
I didn't know it,
but it did.

51:36.461 --> 51:39.495
I give up.
Denzel Washington.

51:39.497 --> 51:41.597
- What?
- Not Denzel?

51:41.599 --> 51:43.766
It's not a fucking
impersonation.

51:43.768 --> 51:45.668
I'm leaving
if you do that again.

51:45.670 --> 51:47.670
You hear me?
Fucking control yourself.

51:47.672 --> 51:49.205
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

51:49.207 --> 51:51.941
Um...

51:51.943 --> 51:55.311
Something bad
has happened.

51:55.313 --> 51:58.280
I'm in trouble.

51:58.282 --> 51:59.482
Now you're scaring me.

51:59.484 --> 52:01.851
It's 'cause I'm scared.

52:04.521 --> 52:06.689
Now, look,

52:06.691 --> 52:09.024
whatever I say for the rest
of this conversation,

52:09.026 --> 52:10.493
just act normal.

52:10.495 --> 52:12.394
You're the one who's slamming
the table and making a scene.

52:12.396 --> 52:14.463
Okay, I don't want to get
into a fucking debate about it.

52:14.465 --> 52:16.165
- Just act regular.
- Okay. Okay.

52:18.535 --> 52:20.102
A man was killed.

52:20.104 --> 52:21.203
A man?
What man?

52:21.205 --> 52:23.272
Just some man.

52:23.274 --> 52:25.574
And the thing is,

52:25.576 --> 52:27.843
I'm being framed for it.

52:27.845 --> 52:29.545
Or being threatened
to be framed for it.

52:29.547 --> 52:30.746
Framed?
Framed by who?

52:30.748 --> 52:33.949
What the fuck are
you talking about?

52:39.589 --> 52:43.559
J.J.
That's who.

52:43.561 --> 52:45.027
J.J.?
Why would J.J. frame you?

52:45.029 --> 52:46.929
I thought he wanted to
go into business with you.

52:46.931 --> 52:50.666
He wants to own Bud's
and me.

52:50.668 --> 52:53.669
And I should have known.
J.J. doesn't have partners.

52:53.671 --> 52:56.205
Can he frame--
how would--

52:56.207 --> 52:59.375
how would he frame you?

52:59.377 --> 53:01.210
My prints are on
the murder weapon.

53:01.212 --> 53:04.747
- Murder--
- Shh.

53:04.749 --> 53:08.083
Roberto had me
hand him his gun.

53:08.085 --> 53:11.453
Roberto left the gun behind
for the cops to find.

53:11.455 --> 53:13.856
They got me walking in
on tape,

53:13.858 --> 53:18.160
but that's not the tape
the cops have yet.

53:18.162 --> 53:20.196
I don't know what
you're talking about,

53:20.198 --> 53:21.897
but what are you gonna do?

53:21.899 --> 53:23.966
Roberto's coming by
to pick me up later.

53:23.968 --> 53:26.402
We're supposed to go
on our rounds.

53:26.404 --> 53:28.404
So we call the cops.

53:28.406 --> 53:30.706
My cousin Reggie on the force
in Hoboken.

53:30.708 --> 53:33.542
They got me on tape,
Ellen.

53:33.544 --> 53:36.545
My prints are on the gun.

53:36.547 --> 53:37.813
They got me.

53:37.815 --> 53:39.248
These guys are pros
at the game.

53:39.250 --> 53:40.516
I'm a layman.

53:40.518 --> 53:42.985
Your cousin Reggie
can't do shit.

53:54.264 --> 53:56.966
Who died?

54:00.403 --> 54:03.138
He was a schoolteacher.

54:05.309 --> 54:06.342
Shh.
Shh. Shh.

54:07.478 --> 54:09.144
Don't cry.
Don't cry.

54:09.146 --> 54:10.613
A schoolteacher?

54:10.615 --> 54:12.014
Yeah,
he was also a cokehead,

54:12.016 --> 54:13.983
if that helps.

54:13.985 --> 54:16.852
Come on.
Hey. Use this napkin.

54:16.854 --> 54:21.390
Come on, just act like
everything is everyday ordinary.

54:21.392 --> 54:23.259
Oh, now you want ordinary.

54:41.812 --> 54:44.713
That's good.

54:44.715 --> 54:46.649
Don't get hit.

54:48.785 --> 54:51.553
Don't get hit.

54:51.555 --> 54:53.389
Come on. Push me back.

54:55.426 --> 54:59.094
All right,
pivot off the front.

54:59.096 --> 55:02.331
Pivot off the back.

55:02.333 --> 55:04.400
Pivot off the front
again.

55:04.402 --> 55:05.434
Off the back.

55:07.938 --> 55:09.471
Some water now?

55:09.473 --> 55:11.707
Not yet.
Come on.

55:30.393 --> 55:32.428
Hey, there.

55:32.430 --> 55:35.998
Ellen's walking Silly.

55:36.000 --> 55:38.000
And at Pittsburgh,
there wasn't much else to do

55:38.002 --> 55:40.169
but learn to pick locks.

55:40.171 --> 55:42.604
In fact, this place reminds me
a lot of Pittsburgh.

55:42.606 --> 55:44.940
Faint smell of
Dutch elm disease.

55:44.942 --> 55:46.642
What do you want?

55:48.112 --> 55:49.745
Well, a cup of coffee
would be kind.

55:49.747 --> 55:51.647
It's chilly in here,
Bud.

55:53.616 --> 55:55.150
There's some coffee
on the stove,

55:55.152 --> 55:57.953
if you don't mind it
not being fresh or gourmet.

55:57.955 --> 56:00.556
Not being fresh or gourmet
is fine.

56:00.558 --> 56:02.925
It will complete the experience
of this apartment.

56:02.927 --> 56:04.793
Is the building a landmark?

56:04.795 --> 56:06.995
I don't know.

56:06.997 --> 56:09.998
Worn flights of stone stairs
look like they've seen wars.

56:10.000 --> 56:11.633
I bet, you excavate
the basement,

56:11.635 --> 56:15.237
there'd be armloads of tumbrel
and peasant rags.

56:15.239 --> 56:17.106
I'm sure some fool
wants to preserve it.

56:17.108 --> 56:20.409
It's dark in here, but did you
lose a few pounds?

56:20.411 --> 56:22.010
Possible.
Yeah.

56:22.012 --> 56:24.179
Kid Sunshine, sometimes
it seems like he's training me.

56:25.383 --> 56:27.383
Or maybe you're having
a nervous breakdown.

56:27.385 --> 56:29.551
That'll make people lose weight
sometimes, if you're lucky.

56:29.553 --> 56:30.753
Yeah, maybe that's it.

56:30.755 --> 56:32.121
Kid Sunshine,

56:32.123 --> 56:34.723
I wanted to talk to you
about him.

56:34.725 --> 56:37.092
What do you want to talk
about Kid Sunshine for?

56:37.094 --> 56:40.796
Well, he's got to fall down,
Bud.

57:14.230 --> 57:16.265
Ow.

57:16.267 --> 57:17.800
You weren't kidding
about this coffee.

57:17.802 --> 57:18.901
You got any sugar?

57:18.903 --> 57:20.402
We're all out.

57:21.971 --> 57:23.972
In the first round,
to be exact.

57:23.974 --> 57:25.374
You put your money
on Kid Sunshine,

57:25.376 --> 57:27.075
you're gonna come out
like gangbusters.

57:27.077 --> 57:28.510
That's an inside tip.

57:28.512 --> 57:31.413
This is a great fighter
we're talking about.

57:31.415 --> 57:32.981
He's gonna win.

57:32.983 --> 57:34.883
Oh, that's kindly of you.
The insider's tip--

57:34.885 --> 57:36.785
Let me give you
an inside tip.

57:36.787 --> 57:38.720
I don't dig
taking chances.

57:38.722 --> 57:40.155
I dig sure things.

57:40.157 --> 57:41.623
If Kid goes down
in the first

57:41.625 --> 57:43.926
and I got a ton of money
on him going down in the first,

57:43.928 --> 57:45.561
that is very sure.

57:45.563 --> 57:47.529
Yeah, but is that believable?
In the first round?

57:47.531 --> 57:49.431
That's gonna be shady
to the commission.

57:49.433 --> 57:50.899
Come on.

57:50.901 --> 57:52.401
All fighters are vulnerable
in the first round.

57:52.403 --> 57:53.936
You know that, Bud.
I don't need to tell you.

57:53.938 --> 57:55.437
Hmm, especially
with two knockout guys.

57:55.439 --> 57:57.639
Hell, if you told me Mercury
went down in the first,

57:57.641 --> 58:01.210
I'd believe you, but
it's not gonna be Mercury.

58:03.279 --> 58:06.315
We, um--
we sent the footage of you

58:06.317 --> 58:10.185
in the lobby on the West End
to one of my pocket cops,

58:10.187 --> 58:11.920
and if Kid doesn't go down
in the first,

58:11.922 --> 58:13.288
the tape turns up
immediately,

58:13.290 --> 58:15.891
and the superintendent
will tell the cops that

58:15.893 --> 58:18.694
you threatened to kill him,
thus the cover-up

58:18.696 --> 58:20.796
and the fake tape.

58:22.233 --> 58:25.801
Super used to be
a soap opera actor.

58:25.803 --> 58:29.171
He's quite convincing,
actually.

58:31.641 --> 58:34.009
Come on now.

58:34.011 --> 58:37.479
Hey, hey, hey.

58:37.481 --> 58:39.481
You caught sight of
this side of darkness before.

58:39.483 --> 58:41.717
You knew it was there.
Don't act like a birthday boy.

58:41.719 --> 58:43.619
Yeah, maybe.
Maybe. I just--

58:43.621 --> 58:46.321
why--why do you always want
to send it all to hell so often?

58:46.323 --> 58:48.991
Hell, my friend, is rising
first thing in the morning

58:48.993 --> 58:50.125
and throughout the day.

58:50.127 --> 58:51.793
I'm just a surfer.

58:51.795 --> 58:52.961
Can't you see that?

58:52.963 --> 58:54.663
No, I guess I can't.

58:54.665 --> 58:57.833
Mmm.
Really?

58:57.835 --> 58:59.468
I think you can.

58:59.470 --> 59:02.471
I think you've surfed some
yourself.

59:02.473 --> 59:06.241
Only difference is,
you got rolled.

59:07.877 --> 59:10.212
How about
the Yankees signing, huh?

59:10.214 --> 59:12.848
Looks like they just bought
themselves another championship.

59:12.850 --> 59:16.318
And people say
boxing is crooked.

59:16.320 --> 59:19.021
Prevaricators.

59:26.763 --> 59:30.065
Are we having
an awkward moment?

59:32.635 --> 59:34.136
If it's any consolation,

59:34.138 --> 59:35.837
a lot of the money
we make off Kid

59:35.839 --> 59:37.172
will go straight to
Bud's Place.

59:37.174 --> 59:39.007
I've sketched out
some design stuff.

59:39.009 --> 59:41.376
I'm thinking linoleum,
hyperborean-style.

59:41.378 --> 59:43.745
I know we said it'd be the same
as it is here in Manhattan,

59:43.747 --> 59:46.682
but I need to express
myself creatively,

59:46.684 --> 59:48.183
and a few
clued-in alterations,

59:48.185 --> 59:51.920
I'm gonna make it fit in
better in Manhattan.

59:57.528 --> 59:59.027
Bud's needs some irony

59:59.029 --> 1:00:00.896
if it's gonna fly downtown.

1:00:00.898 --> 1:00:03.265
As it is,
it's too sincere.

1:00:09.606 --> 1:00:11.907
Also, we'll have
$1/2 million set aside

1:00:11.909 --> 1:00:13.909
for Kid,
to take the edge off.

1:00:13.911 --> 1:00:15.744
He's got the whole world
ahead of him.

1:00:15.746 --> 1:00:17.446
You can't stand it.

1:00:21.784 --> 1:00:24.486
Are you analyzing me?

1:00:28.625 --> 1:00:31.326
Don't hurt yourself.

1:00:35.398 --> 1:00:36.531
Tell Kid to call me.

1:00:36.533 --> 1:00:38.433
Confirmation call.

1:00:38.435 --> 1:00:39.935
Put me at ease.

1:01:16.305 --> 1:01:19.708
There's a long limousine
driving by outside.

1:01:21.277 --> 1:01:24.012
I looked in,
but the windows were darkened.

1:01:24.014 --> 1:01:26.048
Thought it was Bruce.

1:01:26.050 --> 1:01:28.583
Yeah,
I don't think so.

1:01:28.585 --> 1:01:29.985
Yeah, you're right.

1:01:29.987 --> 1:01:31.420
The Boss wouldn't be
so ostentatious.

1:01:31.422 --> 1:01:33.655
Sure he would.

1:01:33.657 --> 1:01:35.924
The Boss has hair plugs.

1:01:35.926 --> 1:01:38.193
- No way.
- Yeah.

1:01:38.195 --> 1:01:39.528
Bruce Springsteen
has hair plugs?

1:01:39.530 --> 1:01:41.096
All those guys have hair plugs.

1:01:41.098 --> 1:01:42.597
No way.

1:01:45.436 --> 1:01:47.402
You have dinner?

1:01:47.404 --> 1:01:50.372
No. I'm not hungry.

1:01:53.343 --> 1:01:56.111
I'm gonna go
take a shower.

1:02:17.334 --> 1:02:19.701
Can I get in with you?

1:02:19.703 --> 1:02:21.136
Sure.

1:02:54.270 --> 1:02:56.238
I know it's only lukewarm.

1:02:56.240 --> 1:02:59.307
It's fine.

1:03:01.477 --> 1:03:03.345
You want to hear
some neat stuff I read

1:03:03.347 --> 1:03:05.614
about the Fuji River?

1:03:26.335 --> 1:03:28.537
You remember
that TV show we saw

1:03:28.539 --> 1:03:32.574
about Sonny Liston
and the phantom punch?

1:03:32.576 --> 1:03:35.177
A lot of fighters have dropped
for money.

1:03:35.179 --> 1:03:39.247
A lot of good guys.
It's complicated.

1:03:39.249 --> 1:03:43.618
You have to consider
the men we deal with.

1:03:43.620 --> 1:03:46.254
You didn't drop.

1:03:49.759 --> 1:03:52.627
Yeah, I guess
I was fortunate that way.

1:03:55.097 --> 1:03:58.633
I think
you have to tell Lou.

1:03:58.635 --> 1:03:59.935
No.

1:03:59.937 --> 1:04:04.372
If I tell Lou,
he'll have Kid take the fall.

1:04:04.374 --> 1:04:08.677
He's not gonna let me do
another round.

1:04:08.679 --> 1:04:11.513
Kid Sunshine would be crushed
if he wasn't champ?

1:04:11.515 --> 1:04:15.217
Not even about that
for him.

1:04:15.219 --> 1:04:17.919
If he wins,
it's not about him.

1:04:17.921 --> 1:04:20.822
It's about something else.

1:04:20.824 --> 1:04:23.058
I can't explain it.
It's--

1:04:24.494 --> 1:04:26.294
I wish I was like that
when I was a fighter.

1:04:26.296 --> 1:04:28.597
I wasn't.
I was up here.

1:04:28.599 --> 1:04:32.567
Big ideas.
Big ideas.

1:04:32.569 --> 1:04:34.769
I used to make fun of stuff.

1:04:36.706 --> 1:04:39.107
And when people's
love for me cracked

1:04:39.109 --> 1:04:42.277
and I saw that love
for what it was,

1:04:42.279 --> 1:04:45.380
I called them
"player haters."

1:04:45.382 --> 1:04:48.950
"Haters gonna hate,"
I used to say.

1:04:50.720 --> 1:04:54.155
What a stupid thing it is
to be a player.

1:04:54.157 --> 1:04:55.523
"Meanwhile,
in your life,

1:04:55.525 --> 1:04:59.127
"you hardly notice the world
around you.

1:04:59.129 --> 1:05:01.496
"Lights changing,

1:05:01.498 --> 1:05:05.500
"sirens dying
along the buildings,

1:05:05.502 --> 1:05:10.639
"your eyes intent on a sight
you do not see yet.

1:05:10.641 --> 1:05:14.943
"Not yet there, as long as
you're only yourself,

1:05:14.945 --> 1:05:17.746
"with whom,
as you recall,

1:05:17.748 --> 1:05:22.484
you were never happy
to be left alone for long."

1:05:26.656 --> 1:05:28.156
I don't know
if that was a poem

1:05:28.158 --> 1:05:31.860
or you're just talking
really great tonight.

1:05:31.862 --> 1:05:33.061
Bud?

1:05:33.063 --> 1:05:34.863
Yeah?

1:05:34.865 --> 1:05:36.231
That sweatshirt stinks.

1:05:36.233 --> 1:05:37.532
- Does it?
- Yeah.

1:05:37.534 --> 1:05:39.601
- Sorry.
- I'm doing laundry tomorrow.

1:05:39.603 --> 1:05:41.002
Could you put it
in the bag?

1:05:41.004 --> 1:05:42.370
Yeah.

1:05:46.075 --> 1:05:47.542
Now, you always do laundry.

1:05:47.544 --> 1:05:50.211
I should do that stuff
sometimes.

1:05:50.213 --> 1:05:52.280
I don't mind it.

1:05:53.950 --> 1:05:55.784
It's peaceful,

1:05:55.786 --> 1:05:57.585
the laundromat.

1:05:57.587 --> 1:06:01.256
Everything whirling
around in soap.

1:06:01.258 --> 1:06:02.424
I read.

1:06:02.426 --> 1:06:03.692
Do you ever think that

1:06:03.694 --> 1:06:05.160
you'll just go through
this life

1:06:05.162 --> 1:06:08.496
and be forgotten?

1:06:08.498 --> 1:06:12.867
Well, we'll all be forgotten
regardless.

1:06:12.869 --> 1:06:14.736
Even the most famous person,

1:06:14.738 --> 1:06:16.938
someday, no one will know
they were here.

1:06:16.940 --> 1:06:19.741
Brad Pitt, someday,
all his movies will be dust.

1:06:19.743 --> 1:06:21.109
That's fucking depressing.

1:06:21.111 --> 1:06:24.846
I don't think so.

1:06:24.848 --> 1:06:27.115
You should read this book
I'm reading.

1:06:27.117 --> 1:06:31.419
It's all about how the ego
suckers us into thinking

1:06:31.421 --> 1:06:35.390
that we're all separate
from each other.

1:06:35.392 --> 1:06:38.493
But actually,
in reality,

1:06:38.495 --> 1:06:42.497
you, me,
this bed,

1:06:42.499 --> 1:06:43.932
this wall...

1:06:43.934 --> 1:06:45.066
Silly--

1:06:45.068 --> 1:06:46.568
Don't say her name.
She'll wake up.

1:06:46.570 --> 1:06:49.671
We're all
the same thing.

1:06:49.673 --> 1:06:52.507
We're not separate at all.

1:06:52.509 --> 1:06:56.044
And this is all
just our mind.

1:06:57.780 --> 1:07:01.149
Is that supposed
to be solacing?

1:07:01.151 --> 1:07:03.852
No.

1:07:03.854 --> 1:07:06.454
It is what it is.

1:07:06.456 --> 1:07:11.159
If this is our mind,
the mind is a scary place.

1:07:11.161 --> 1:07:13.628
It can be.

1:07:13.630 --> 1:07:16.164
Well, there's no way out,
so...

1:07:16.166 --> 1:07:19.067
might as well
learn to enjoy it.

1:07:21.437 --> 1:07:25.974
You got any ideas about
a good way to enjoy it?

1:08:08.785 --> 1:08:11.686
Is that your car?

1:08:11.688 --> 1:08:13.121
Yeah.

1:08:14.591 --> 1:08:17.158
Is there someone in it?

1:10:16.345 --> 1:10:17.979
What's wrong?

1:10:17.981 --> 1:10:19.080
You're sad.

1:10:19.082 --> 1:10:20.782
Well,

1:10:20.784 --> 1:10:22.150
lonely.

1:10:24.620 --> 1:10:26.521
Maybe it's just it being
Christmas Eve and all.

1:10:26.523 --> 1:10:29.490
I get lonely
around Christmas.

1:10:29.492 --> 1:10:31.392
They kill so many trees.

1:10:31.394 --> 1:10:33.695
Statistics
are reprehensible.

1:10:36.465 --> 1:10:37.899
Oh, shit.
Did you hear that?

1:10:37.901 --> 1:10:40.068
What?

1:10:40.070 --> 1:10:41.736
I think I hear

1:10:41.738 --> 1:10:43.838
thousands of trees crying.

1:10:43.840 --> 1:10:44.639
Shut up.

1:10:45.642 --> 1:10:47.308
It's not funny.

1:10:47.310 --> 1:10:50.278
- It's a little funny.
- It's not funny!

1:10:50.280 --> 1:10:53.448
Asshole.

1:10:53.450 --> 1:10:54.449
Oh, yeah?

1:10:54.451 --> 1:10:58.386
Oh, yeah, bring it.

1:11:00.756 --> 1:11:02.223
This is the most gourmet shit
I ever had.

1:11:02.225 --> 1:11:05.727
I can't seem to find
my appetite for it.

1:11:05.729 --> 1:11:07.095
What is that again?

1:11:07.097 --> 1:11:10.598
It's...scallops
with raisins, basically.

1:11:11.601 --> 1:11:12.900
What's that?

1:11:12.902 --> 1:11:15.136
This is the egg caviar.

1:11:15.138 --> 1:11:16.137
Good?

1:11:16.139 --> 1:11:17.138
No.

1:11:17.941 --> 1:11:19.173
You ever had caviar before?

1:11:19.175 --> 1:11:20.375
No.

1:11:20.377 --> 1:11:21.843
I figured as long as
the hotel is paying for it,

1:11:21.845 --> 1:11:24.279
I should try it,
but...

1:11:24.281 --> 1:11:25.513
it's kind of funky.

1:11:26.983 --> 1:11:28.583
You know, Kid can't eat
before his weigh-in,

1:11:28.585 --> 1:11:33.021
but he's not missing much.

1:11:33.023 --> 1:11:34.589
You got a phone call
this morning

1:11:34.591 --> 1:11:36.090
from a woman named Mae.

1:11:36.092 --> 1:11:38.059
You were out with Silly.
It was an unknown number.

1:11:38.061 --> 1:11:39.761
I thought it might be best
if I answered,

1:11:39.763 --> 1:11:42.630
considering everything
that's going on.

1:11:42.632 --> 1:11:44.666
She sounded very strange
when she heard my voice.

1:11:44.668 --> 1:11:46.367
Then she said,

1:11:46.369 --> 1:11:48.670
"Merry Christmas"
and to wish you luck.

1:11:48.672 --> 1:11:49.871
That's all.

1:11:49.873 --> 1:11:51.639
Okay.

1:11:51.641 --> 1:11:53.174
- She works for J.J., right?
- Yeah.

1:11:53.176 --> 1:11:55.276
- I think I've seen her before.
- Yeah, yeah, probably.

1:11:55.278 --> 1:11:57.545
She was at some of my fights
back in the day.

1:11:57.547 --> 1:11:59.614
Look up at me, Bud.

1:12:01.884 --> 1:12:04.285
When people ask about you,

1:12:04.287 --> 1:12:07.989
I don't tell them
everything that I know.

1:12:07.991 --> 1:12:10.892
You haven't always
been good to me.

1:12:12.194 --> 1:12:13.895
Breaks my heart.

1:12:16.832 --> 1:12:20.168
I love you so much,
but...

1:12:20.170 --> 1:12:24.072
I don't know if I can
be your girl anymore.

1:12:32.181 --> 1:12:34.282
I'll always be
your friend,

1:12:34.284 --> 1:12:36.951
but--

1:12:36.953 --> 1:12:39.120
I got to look out for myself
a little bit.

1:12:39.122 --> 1:12:40.822
You know?

1:12:56.338 --> 1:13:00.408
All those lights
and all those buildings...

1:13:02.077 --> 1:13:06.080
You know, if I--
if I could do it over again,

1:13:06.082 --> 1:13:09.617
I'd do it--
I would have married you.

1:13:09.619 --> 1:13:11.619
I would have had
a little baby with you.

1:13:11.621 --> 1:13:14.789
No, you wouldn't,
Bud.

1:13:14.791 --> 1:13:17.125
You're gonna do this
to me now?

1:13:17.127 --> 1:13:18.860
Out of nowhere,
you're just gonna do this?

1:13:18.862 --> 1:13:20.361
You're supposed to be
my fucking friend.

1:13:20.363 --> 1:13:22.430
You know I'm your
fucking friend.

1:13:22.432 --> 1:13:23.931
We're not happy, Bud.

1:13:23.933 --> 1:13:25.066
You fuck around on me.

1:13:25.068 --> 1:13:26.401
So you don't love me
anymore?

1:13:26.403 --> 1:13:27.769
I'll always love you.

1:13:27.771 --> 1:13:29.604
But you're not, like,
in love with me anymore?

1:13:29.606 --> 1:13:31.105
Not--not enough
to make it work.

1:13:31.107 --> 1:13:32.673
'Cause if you were
in love with me,

1:13:32.675 --> 1:13:35.209
we could make this function;
I-I could change.

1:13:35.211 --> 1:13:36.244
People can change.

1:13:36.246 --> 1:13:37.879
That's the whole Buddha thing,
right?

1:13:37.881 --> 1:13:39.480
I mean, things are always
changing.

1:13:39.482 --> 1:13:42.216
A couple months ago, you said,
"Let's do couples therapy."

1:13:42.218 --> 1:13:44.152
I said no, like a fuck-head,
but I would do it.

1:13:44.154 --> 1:13:48.856
I would do that couples
therapy shit with you.

1:13:48.858 --> 1:13:50.291
So you're gonna leave me too,
huh?

1:13:50.293 --> 1:13:51.959
You're gonna turn on me
just like everyone else

1:13:51.961 --> 1:13:53.194
now that I'm not
the man anymore.

1:13:53.196 --> 1:13:54.896
That shit is in your head,
Bud.

1:13:54.898 --> 1:13:57.131
That is your dumb
ESPN-conditioned version

1:13:57.133 --> 1:13:59.200
of the universe where
you're completely dependent

1:13:59.202 --> 1:14:01.202
on outside circumstances
and just crumble

1:14:01.204 --> 1:14:04.071
the second someone
doesn't bow to you.

1:14:04.073 --> 1:14:06.908
I loved you despite all that
neurotic, infantile

1:14:06.910 --> 1:14:09.043
football shit.

1:14:28.397 --> 1:14:30.731
It's icy streets.
Careful driving. Okay?

1:14:30.733 --> 1:14:32.500
Okay.

1:14:36.839 --> 1:14:38.306
Hey, when you walk Silly,
just make sure

1:14:38.308 --> 1:14:40.007
she doesn't eat anything
off the street.

1:14:40.009 --> 1:14:41.542
I know. I know.
I won't.

1:14:41.544 --> 1:14:43.010
'Cause she wants to eat, like,
chicken bones and shit.

1:14:43.012 --> 1:14:44.412
That stuff will kill her.

1:14:44.414 --> 1:14:46.080
I'm the one who told you
about the chicken bones.

1:14:46.082 --> 1:14:47.582
You really are a fruitcake
if you think that's true.

1:14:47.584 --> 1:14:49.383
Wow. I'm not even getting
into that with you.

1:14:49.385 --> 1:14:51.018
You're fucking nuts
if you think that,

1:14:51.020 --> 1:14:52.553
because I told you
about the chicken bones

1:14:52.555 --> 1:14:54.088
when I first met Silly
'cause you had no idea.

1:14:54.090 --> 1:14:55.623
Okay, whatever you say,
cuckoo.

1:14:55.625 --> 1:14:57.625
Just--I mean,
the main thing is,

1:14:57.627 --> 1:14:59.093
we agree on her diet.

1:14:59.095 --> 1:15:00.495
I won't let her
eat off the street.

1:15:00.497 --> 1:15:01.496
- Okay, I promise.
- Okay.

1:16:11.568 --> 1:16:13.334
Hello?

1:16:14.803 --> 1:16:18.139
My mom always told me
to stay in Montana.

1:16:18.141 --> 1:16:21.576
I thought Montana
was for squares.

1:16:21.578 --> 1:16:24.545
I had a poster of the
Chrysler Building in my room.

1:16:24.547 --> 1:16:26.247
Stared at it for hours.

1:16:26.249 --> 1:16:29.817
Metal and stainless steel.

1:16:29.819 --> 1:16:31.185
My goal was to come here

1:16:31.187 --> 1:16:33.821
and become one of those
Chrysler eagles.

1:16:33.823 --> 1:16:35.890
Who knows?

1:16:35.892 --> 1:16:38.960
Maybe I achieved my goal.

1:16:44.967 --> 1:16:46.400
I know it was J.J.

1:16:46.402 --> 1:16:48.669
who had you go down that night
in the fifth.

1:16:48.671 --> 1:16:51.172
Even Lou Powell bought it
'cause you got hit so hard

1:16:51.174 --> 1:16:53.207
and you were known
for being chinny.

1:16:53.209 --> 1:16:58.079
You didn't open your restaurant
on bank loans.

1:16:58.081 --> 1:17:00.514
Look, I'm not judgy.
I understand.

1:17:00.516 --> 1:17:03.050
You wanted to get out
while your brain worked

1:17:03.052 --> 1:17:05.219
and still have something
to show for it.

1:17:05.221 --> 1:17:08.122
You could win more by losing.

1:17:17.499 --> 1:17:20.501
You know, we could have
a really good time.

1:17:20.503 --> 1:17:21.602
Don't be so prideful.

1:17:21.604 --> 1:17:23.437
Sometimes I get
these headaches.

1:17:23.439 --> 1:17:25.439
I used to tell myself
it was because of the punch,

1:17:25.441 --> 1:17:29.176
but I think a person's
conscience can take on

1:17:29.178 --> 1:17:32.346
all sorts of physical
manifestations.

1:17:32.348 --> 1:17:34.649
J.J. always said
you're one of the smart ones.

1:17:34.651 --> 1:17:35.883
Maybe too smart.

1:17:35.885 --> 1:17:37.184
No such thing.

1:17:37.186 --> 1:17:39.553
Yeah, I don't know
about that.

1:17:39.555 --> 1:17:41.589
But, you know,
if I get a good lawyer--

1:17:41.591 --> 1:17:43.491
I'm guilty of a lot of things,
but murder's not one of them.

1:17:43.493 --> 1:17:46.827
You don't want
to fight him.

1:17:46.829 --> 1:17:48.829
You know, you're looking at me
like I'm ugly.

1:17:48.831 --> 1:17:50.131
Wasn't I pretty yesterday?

1:17:50.133 --> 1:17:52.366
You still are.
I'm somewhere else.

1:17:52.368 --> 1:17:55.903
God, I wish
I could convince you.

1:17:55.905 --> 1:17:57.238
The times we'd have...

1:17:57.240 --> 1:17:59.240
Yeah?
You'd take me to Montana?

1:17:59.242 --> 1:18:00.474
Show me the fields?

1:18:00.476 --> 1:18:01.776
If you wanted.

1:18:01.778 --> 1:18:03.310
I'm not completely sure
if they're still there

1:18:03.312 --> 1:18:05.012
or if I could even
find them.

1:18:05.014 --> 1:18:07.214
They're still there.

1:18:07.216 --> 1:18:09.417
I think I'm all
turned around.

1:18:11.420 --> 1:18:14.622
I should get back
to Kid.

1:18:18.026 --> 1:18:21.095
Don't try to go straight
on a crooked road.

1:18:21.097 --> 1:18:23.664
You'll only get flattened.

1:18:43.619 --> 1:18:46.854
Bud?

1:19:06.476 --> 1:19:09.210
Sir, do me a favor
and turn off the music.

1:19:09.212 --> 1:19:11.378
Sorry. What?

1:19:11.380 --> 1:19:13.914
Sir, do me a favor.
Turn off the music.

1:19:13.916 --> 1:19:16.984
You want me--
you want another station?

1:19:16.986 --> 1:19:18.586
No station.

1:19:44.647 --> 1:19:46.747
Hey, Kid's not taking
any visitors.

1:19:46.749 --> 1:19:47.882
Sorry.

1:19:47.884 --> 1:19:51.552
I'm visiting you.
Not Kid.

1:19:56.491 --> 1:19:58.459
J.J. asked me
to check in with you.

1:19:59.661 --> 1:20:01.328
You checked in.

1:20:05.967 --> 1:20:08.903
Is there a trace of defiance
in your demeanor,

1:20:08.905 --> 1:20:10.771
or did I mistake?

1:20:10.773 --> 1:20:11.939
You mistake.

1:20:11.941 --> 1:20:13.407
Look, what can I do for you?

1:20:13.409 --> 1:20:16.177
Why are you acting like
you don't know me, man?

1:20:16.179 --> 1:20:18.512
I'm not.

1:20:18.514 --> 1:20:20.848
Whatever, dude.
Be that way.

1:20:22.918 --> 1:20:25.419
Kid never called J.J.

1:20:25.421 --> 1:20:27.655
That's somewhat discourteous,
don't you think?

1:20:27.657 --> 1:20:28.789
Discourteous?

1:20:28.791 --> 1:20:31.292
I'm sure he didn't mean it
that way.

1:20:31.294 --> 1:20:34.094
So it's just an oversight?

1:20:34.096 --> 1:20:35.896
The kid's gonna do
what he's supposed to do?

1:20:35.898 --> 1:20:37.231
Kid's gonna do what
he's supposed to do.

1:20:37.233 --> 1:20:40.434
Actually, I should
get back to Kid.

1:20:40.436 --> 1:20:42.970
Hell, why do you have to
get back to Kid?

1:20:42.972 --> 1:20:45.306
Get back to Kid.

1:20:45.308 --> 1:20:46.640
I can't believe
you're gonna act

1:20:46.642 --> 1:20:49.643
all cold and shit
with me, man.

1:20:49.645 --> 1:20:52.112
Your fucking dice
are loaded.

1:20:52.114 --> 1:20:55.449
Make no mistake,
people like us,

1:20:55.451 --> 1:21:00.421
we're made to go to war
as entertainment for the rich.

1:21:00.423 --> 1:21:03.924
This world is run by a pack
of ferociously ambitious

1:21:03.926 --> 1:21:07.928
teenage girls
at the Saint Anne School.

1:21:07.930 --> 1:21:10.931
This shit going down,
honor just don't apply.

1:21:10.933 --> 1:21:14.535
There ain't no fucking honor
possible in this situation.

1:21:14.537 --> 1:21:17.171
It's, are you smart,
or are you stupid?

1:21:17.173 --> 1:21:18.505
And you're smart, Spartacus.

1:21:18.507 --> 1:21:19.874
So don't be stupid.

1:21:19.876 --> 1:21:21.041
Okay.

1:21:21.043 --> 1:21:22.910
'Cause you're fucking smart.

1:21:24.946 --> 1:21:28.515
They didn't count on
chop-shop parts like us--

1:21:28.517 --> 1:21:31.886
motherfuckers with fox brains
to outwit the system.

1:21:33.822 --> 1:21:36.190
I know it seems like I'm asking
you to betray your friend,

1:21:36.192 --> 1:21:37.591
but what I'm really
asking you to do

1:21:37.593 --> 1:21:39.493
is to be enterprising
and entrepreneurial,

1:21:39.495 --> 1:21:42.863
because suffice it to say
that I fucking love you, man.

1:21:46.534 --> 1:21:49.670
So I'll see you
after the fight.

1:21:49.672 --> 1:21:52.873
Condolences to Lou
and Kid.

1:21:54.209 --> 1:21:56.543
And, hey, man,
J.J. says you got to get

1:21:56.545 --> 1:21:58.712
your Twitter follower numbers
way up.

1:21:58.714 --> 1:22:00.881
You got, like,
no one following you.

1:22:00.883 --> 1:22:03.918
And you're tweeting
in the wind.

1:22:18.266 --> 1:22:21.068
Who was that?

1:22:21.070 --> 1:22:23.837
Roberto, J.J.'s guy.

1:22:26.474 --> 1:22:28.509
What'd he want?

1:22:34.849 --> 1:22:36.550
Plainly see he's overwhelmed.

1:22:36.552 --> 1:22:38.352
Mercury Williams
has too much power...

1:22:38.354 --> 1:22:41.021
Everyone's going one way;
you're going the other.

1:22:41.023 --> 1:22:42.022
- What?
- Where to?

1:22:42.024 --> 1:22:43.290
Nowhere.

1:22:43.292 --> 1:22:44.692
Could you just, like,
drive around?

1:22:44.694 --> 1:22:45.893
- You want to see the sights?
- No, no, no.

1:22:45.895 --> 1:22:47.161
I've seen the sights.

1:22:47.163 --> 1:22:48.462
Just drive around wherever.
Okay?

1:22:48.464 --> 1:22:49.897
You want to turn up
the radio now?

1:22:49.899 --> 1:22:51.699
I got to hear this.

1:22:51.701 --> 1:22:53.934
Yeah, I can turn
the radio up.

1:22:53.936 --> 1:22:56.804
You don't got to
attitudinize me about it.

1:22:56.806 --> 1:22:58.005
Sorry.

1:22:58.007 --> 1:23:00.174
Kid Sunshine grabbing Mercury.

1:23:00.176 --> 1:23:01.942
Holds on to him
for dear life.

1:23:01.944 --> 1:23:03.410
The crowd begins to boo.

1:23:03.412 --> 1:23:05.913
Referee Smith has to
break the fighters up.

1:23:05.915 --> 1:23:08.282
Kid Sunshine's mouth
is bleeding badly.

1:23:08.284 --> 1:23:09.616
Ay-yi-yi.

1:23:09.618 --> 1:23:11.318
Now Smith checks to see...

1:23:11.320 --> 1:23:12.686
It's a massacre.

1:23:12.688 --> 1:23:14.221
If Sunshine can continue.

1:23:14.223 --> 1:23:16.390
And Sunshine is saying he can.

1:23:16.392 --> 1:23:18.792
So here we go.
Fight is back on.

1:23:18.794 --> 1:23:20.694
And here comes Mercury again.

1:23:20.696 --> 1:23:22.162
Mercury comes in
with the left hook.

1:23:22.164 --> 1:23:25.032
Kid Sunshine ducks it.
Hits Mercury in the ribs hard!

1:23:25.034 --> 1:23:27.301
Well, there's some life
from the Kid.

1:23:27.303 --> 1:23:28.969
- Where did that come from?
- Wowee!

1:23:28.971 --> 1:23:31.438
Well, that's what
Mercury Williams is wondering.

1:23:31.440 --> 1:23:32.806
He looks angry.

1:23:32.808 --> 1:23:35.175
He chases Sunshine
into the corner

1:23:35.177 --> 1:23:36.910
and lands
a hard body punch,

1:23:36.912 --> 1:23:39.046
but Sunshine slides out
of the corner

1:23:39.048 --> 1:23:42.549
before Mercury can start
any kind of combination.

1:23:42.551 --> 1:23:44.685
Mercury chases after
the Kid.

1:23:44.687 --> 1:23:46.954
Kid Sunshine stops
in his tracks

1:23:46.956 --> 1:23:48.389
and throws a right hand.

1:23:48.391 --> 1:23:50.190
Was that a right-hand lead?

1:23:50.192 --> 1:23:51.325
I think it was, Joe.

1:23:51.327 --> 1:23:52.960
A right-hand lead!

1:23:52.962 --> 1:23:55.496
- And Mercury Williams is hurt!
- Oh, mama!

1:23:56.899 --> 1:23:58.766
Mercury shakes it off,
comes after Sunshine,

1:23:58.768 --> 1:24:01.168
jabs some at Sunshine's head,
but Sunshine blocks.

1:24:01.170 --> 1:24:02.603
They circle...

1:24:02.605 --> 1:24:04.772
